message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with speaker diarization, which is a subfield of speech processing and analysis. Other likely sub-categories could be cs.CL (computational linguistics) as the paper deals with naturalistic audio streams, cs.LG (machine learning) as the paper proposes a mixture model for clustering, cs.AI (artificial intelligence) as the paper deals with automated speaker recognition, and cs.MM (multimedia) as the paper deals with audio recordings.
